    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey so im working on this script to process some huge csv files with pandas but im getting a MemoryError every time i run it. i think it might be because of how i'm loading the data. can u explain the main difference between using a list comprehension vs a generator function when im trying to loop through these rows? like which one is better for keeping memory usage low?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A list comprehension builds an entire list in memory at once, which is great for small datasets but can cause a MemoryError with huge CSVs. A generator function, on the other hand, produces items one at a time—only when they are requested—meaning it keeps memory usage extremely low. For processing massive files like yours, a generator is the superior choice because it streams the data instead of loading everything simultaneously. This lazy evaluation is key to avoiding those memory constraints.",
      "source": "target",
