      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To track down memory leaks, you'll need specialized profiling tools, as simply observing the code won't reveal the hidden references. Tools like `memory_profiler` or using Python's built-in `tracemalloc` are excellent starting points. You can run your script under these profilers; they will show you exactly which lines of code are allocating memory and, crucially, where those objects are being held onto after they should have been freed.",
